<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Pilsburry:
[B]We do OK damage vs most mobs. So we have some minor solo'ing ability, I mean I can take out maybe 4 mobs in the grey before resting if I am on my horse, have KEI, BaotR, SCM3, MC1, judgement spell. Of course I have FT5 also...and 255wis +1025mana or so and high ac for a cleric so I don't heal myself much.

Still I find it very inefficent. All the other preists and casters are out there with pets doing thier damage mana free, click nuke devices, quad kiting, mana efficent nukes, even more efficent DoT's.

That's where we fall behind...lack of efficent damage dealing besides straight forward nukes.

FYI if you talking to me about Lguk and pre-kunark ratios...you can stop there...I have been hardcore since way before the game went public. I know all about cleric damage pre-release even. Such as the addition of furor (I feedback'd it a a couple times before they added it, 8dmg at level 13 was weak), or the nerfing of AE dmg (used to do more and larger radius). We also used to have a FUNCTIONAL lull spell. Now its just a joke (it was rarely resisted before, gave a failure message if it was, AND didn't agro on failure..ever).

1. I think our LIVE damage nuke is approx where it should be. And it will definately be adaquate if they put a mage nuke focus item effect on a peice of our armor (as well as all other casters armor, casters will remain balanced as is now with eachother...but gain ground on melee DPS)

2. I think our undead nukes are outdated.
Judgement = 325mana --> 925 dmg (2.85)
Exile Undead = 250mana -->725dmg (2.9)
Is that really that much of a better ratio? 0.05? I mean can we really be called the true undead slayer? LOL. not.

Wizards 4.0 on ice spear, 4.44 on bane spells (situational like undead)

Mages are second best nukers..they have a 3.37 ratio at 60. 

Verdict: Our undead nuke should be increased to 1000dmg for 310mana. 3.22 ratio. Why so close? It's not really. This is a situational nuke and it's less efficent then thier general nukes. It's more along the line of bane spells which is a FAR higher ratio, it's specific to undead. So a 3.22 ratio is rather conservative in comparision.

Plus wizards are specialized in evoc for another 8% mana savings. Plus they almost always have fury3 or higher...we have to focus on many other skills first. Wizards over level 34 or so have innate lower resists as well, and more resists to check against..fire, magic, cold...So in all actuallity the gap is still wider then it appears. If you factor all that in the ratio would be more like 3.22 vs undead...VS 5.0 vs all. Big difference.

I'm going to ask you a question now....how many undead mobs are in velious? Exactly. If our nukes are specialized so as to be hard to find an encounter in an entire expansion....then they should do a decent ratio.

3. I think our undead DoT's are too weak to even bother mem'ing. An undead DoT would mainly be used for solo'ing clerics because mobs in groups die too fast. And on raids...well we heal on raids.

4. I think we need something to use against MR mobs. MY melee is ZIPO, NADA..I have no pet to speak of. And all I got is MR nukes and heals...alot of times in icewell and such before raids...I sit at full mana. I can do nothing with it..and there is not enough healing needed (if they upped dmg output or HP any further the zone would be even more barren then now, in addition to cleric nuke immune they are also unslowable)

5. I think we need some sort of mana free damage, nothing spectacular, something that is less useful on groups or raids then it is when solo'ing. In our case all nukes are poor to use on raids, because we are expected to heal. But DoT's are definately less useful on raids.

300-350 dmg in 7-8secs would be a good click item. Preferrably found in a dungeon such as cazic or weaker....obtainable by all clerics just like druid epics etc are. Not a high end raid item. If it must be difficult to obtain a mob similar difficulty to velketor would be acceptable, provided he dropped several random loots for all classes, so that he was "desirable".

Speaking of which, I sure hope they have more dungeons like cazic in the near future. Quite frankly we have out grown dungeons such as velks, sebilis, karnors, acheva...ssra and cazic are the only real single group challange anymore. Ssra is slightly more difficult in some respects...and has crap for loot. Cazic is my idea of a near perfectly balanced high end skilled player exp/camp zone. Although at times I question just how good some of that loot is lol. But the same goes for the new smithed cultural armor...nice stuff is out for those who aren't in uber guilds these days.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
